title.narrative: Component 1; Comprehensive and macroeconomic management; basic statistics on economic performance produced and utilized; data base created by ISTEEBU with BRB

baseline.value: Database is not available and Economic Model is unused

target.value: Comprehensive national accounts produced annually; Basic statistics on economic performance produced in timely basis and utilized;data base created by ISTEEBU in cooperation with BRB

title.narrative: Report containing updated economic data and statistics is available. Legal framework regulating the production and dissemination ofstatistics has been adopted.

baseline.value: The economic report is not published

target.value: Quarterly and Annual economic and financial reports are produced on a timely basis

title.narrative: Component 3: Private sector development and privatization

baseline.value: Washing stations of the Coffee sector to be privatized,

target.value: Assessment and Audit of REGIDESO; settlement of Government arrears; revision of institutional framework for privatization;adoptionand implementation of reform in the coffee sector.

comment.narrative: Privatization of CWS went well; no one was laid off, however, titles still need to be given to investors for purchase of coffeewashing stations.

title.narrative: Component 4: Governance, Public procurement, external Oversight, Judiciary reforms

baseline.value: oversight structures are not operational, tribunal of commerce and arbitration center are not operational

target.value: Legal and juridical reform strategy defined and oversight structures established. MP and media trained; Arbitration centeroperational, Governance strategy adopted, procurement code adopted

comment.narrative: The PSD will fund the database to capture data going from 2009 backwards for at least 10 years.

title.narrative: Parliament and Journalists are trained in budgetary process

baseline.value: Members of the Finance commission in Parliament are not trained

target.value: Increased number of parliamentarians and representatives of Media trained in budget process

comment.narrative: one elections are finished, another training should be provided to parliamentarians

title.narrative: Audit of Government accounts completed on a timely manner,

baseline.value: Audit of the government account is not produced on a standard basis.

target.value: Significant reduction in time lag between closing accounts and submission to the audit court.

title.narrative: Revision of the procurement code and procedures to enhance competition is completed

baseline.value: Competition in the bidding process is weak

target.value: The number of public contracts awarded through procurement process lesscompetitive than the one recommended for the estimatedamount of the contract does not exceed 15 percent

comment.narrative: no further comments. Will be completed on time.

title.narrative: Computerized financial system network is operational (SIGEFI)

baseline.value: The budget is not globally comprehensive as it does not include all projects financed by donors and wage bill

target.value: SIGEFI is operational and include all expenditures. SIGEFI prepares quarterly reports on the budget execution on a timely basis

comment.narrative: SIGEFI is operational and it will be integrated with OBR SIGTAS software.

title.narrative: Legal and Judicial reform strategy defined and adopted

baseline.value: The existing strategy in the justice sector is weak

target.value: Implementation of the recommendations of the diagnostic study

title.narrative: Revision of the budget framework and procedures to improve transparency is completed

baseline.value: The procurement system is not fully transparent

target.value: Number of invitation to tender for which invitation process and attribution of the market are publicly announced exceeds 75 percent

title.narrative: Component 2: Public Finance and Administrative management, Budget execution has improved; share of priority sectors in Budget has increased; wage bill as share of GDP is on declining path.

baseline.value: Audit and studies to be completed; Computerized financial system network is not available; wage bill is more than 10 percent ofthe GDP

target.value: Budget execution has improved; wage bill as share of GDP is declining; revised organic law completed; computerized financialsystemnetwork is operational.

comment.narrative: satisfactory progress. Audits have been completed for 10 enterprises.
